WEBVTT

1
00:41.798 --> 00:43.100
Come in, please.

2
00:44.100 --> 00:46.700
Pierre, it's a call from France,
it's urgent.

3
00:48.298 --> 00:50.100
After the concert.

4
00:54.100 --> 00:56.500
It's about your mother.

5
01:03.500 --> 01:05.500
Yes?

6
01:17.501 --> 01:23.501
Chorists

7
02:59.500 --> 03:01.699
Do you recognise me?

8
03:03.699 --> 03:08.199
Pond Bottom, my father will pick me up on Saturday.

9
03:09.500 --> 03:11.098
Pepinot

10
03:12.098 --> 03:13.900
But of course.

11
03:14.800 --> 03:18.000
Pepinot! How long has it been?

12
03:18.400 --> 03:21.598
Only 50 years.

13
03:23.000 --> 03:25.199
Pond Bottom.

14
03:27.500 --> 03:30.300
There you are, the short one in the first row.

15
03:30.500 --> 03:32.000
And this is you.

16
03:33.199 --> 03:35.199
And the prefect, what was his name?

17
03:35.300 --> 03:37.098
Clement Mathieu

18
03:37.400 --> 03:39.800
Clement Mathieu

19
03:40.900 --> 03:43.199
What became of him?

20
03:45.199 --> 03:46.800
Open it.

21
03:51.598 --> 03:54.300
Pond Bottom-- year 1949

22
03:55.098 --> 03:58.800
This is the diary kept by Mathieu,
about his days at Pond Bottom.

23
03:59.000 --> 04:01.699
About his story, and ours too.

24
04:03.098 --> 04:04.800
He wanted you to have it.

25
04:05.000 --> 04:08.900
I'd prefer to give it to you
under happier circumstances but...

26
04:13.098 --> 04:15.199
1949, Jan. 15th.

27
04:16.199 --> 04:18.899
After a few years of failure,

28
04:19.699 --> 04:22.699
I was certain the worst was yet to come.

29
04:24.199 --> 04:27.899
It was a boarding school for difficult children.

30
04:28.600 --> 04:30.800
At least that's what the ad said.

31
04:31.500 --> 04:33.100
Pond Bottom

32
04:33.500 --> 04:36.399
The school seemed to be named just for me.

33
04:36.899 --> 04:38.199
Good morning.

34
04:40.199 --> 04:42.199
You are alone?

35
04:43.000 --> 04:44.600
What are you doing here?

36
04:45.399 --> 04:47.699
I'm waiting for Saturday.

37
04:48.000 --> 04:49.600
Why?

38
04:50.199 --> 04:52.399
Because my father will come and fetch me.

39
04:52.800 --> 04:55.199
But today is not Saturday.

40
04:56.199 --> 04:58.300
Pepinot!

41
04:58.399 --> 05:02.300
I'm Clement Mathieu, the new prefect.

42
05:04.699 --> 05:06.399
Is this your first prefect position?

43
05:06.500 --> 05:08.100
I once taught in a private school.

44
05:08.399 --> 05:10.399
-What did you teach?
-Music.

45
05:10.600 --> 05:12.600
-You will get on well with Mr. Rachin

46
05:12.699 --> 05:14.800
The Headmaster. He used to play the trumpet.

47
05:15.000 --> 05:16.399
Really?

48
05:16.800 --> 05:19.100
These are his daughters, he lives here.

49
05:21.399 --> 05:25.800
-Have you met him before?
-Not yet, I got the job through Mme Boissement.

50
05:26.000 --> 05:27.100
Really?

51
05:27.500 --> 05:29.600
That was Uncle Maxence

52
05:29.699 --> 05:31.899
He proceeded to explain that he was in charge of...

53
05:32.000 --> 05:35.899
security, first aid,
store room, and window repair.

54
05:37.899 --> 05:39.300
What is he doing?

55
05:39.899 --> 05:41.600
Student punished by Mr Rachin.

56
05:42.300 --> 05:45.300
15 days of community service... Maid work

57
05:45.500 --> 05:47.199
What are the kids like?

58
05:47.399 --> 05:48.899
Didn't they tell you?

59
05:49.100 --> 05:50.000
No.

60
05:51.399 --> 05:54.300
This is the infirmary.
Later I will show you my little vegetable patch.

61
05:54.500 --> 05:55.699
With pleasure.

62
05:58.699 --> 06:01.500
-What have they done this time?
-Let's me help you...

63
06:01.699 --> 06:03.500
Are you Clement Mathieu?

64
06:03.600 --> 06:05.399
The Headmaster.

65
06:05.500 --> 06:07.300
Rachin, Headmaster.

66
06:07.899 --> 06:09.800
Ah, Headmaster, I am sorry.

67
06:10.000 --> 06:11.199
Yes, you are late.

68
06:11.300 --> 06:14.500
-I was given the wrong bus timetable.
-Keeping on time is a basic principle here.

69
06:14.800 --> 06:16.100
Very well.

70
06:16.199 --> 06:17.600
Headmaster.

71
06:18.199 --> 06:19.899
Very well, headmaster.

72
06:20.000 --> 06:21.100
Ok, follow me.

73
06:22.100 --> 06:27.100
I first suggest you learn our regulations.
You will supervise study after 4pm.

74
06:31.500 --> 06:33.500
What's the matter! Answer!

75
06:33.899 --> 06:35.600
-Take this

76
06:35.800 --> 06:38.300
Another trap.
Our pupils' lovely disposition.

77
06:38.399 --> 06:40.399
Let's sit him down there.

78
06:40.899 --> 06:41.899
I can't see.

79
06:42.699 --> 06:45.300
Don't overdo it, let me take a look.

80
06:45.500 --> 06:47.000
Not so good.

81
06:47.300 --> 06:51.100
-You, go ring the bell, call everyone.
-Shouldn't we call a doctor first?

82
06:51.300 --> 06:54.500
You know how much they cost?
What did I tell you, go ring the bell.

83
06:55.000 --> 06:56.100
Where is the bell?

84
06:56.300 --> 06:58.899
Open the door, you'll see it.

85
07:01.899 --> 07:04.699
Everyone here!

86
07:04.701 --> 07:07.500
Everyone here!

87
07:08.300 --> 07:10.000
Does this kind of incident often happen?

88
07:10.000 --> 07:12.199
Ring, just ring the bell.

89
07:26.199 --> 07:28.800
Everyone in the yard!

90
07:34.800 --> 07:37.699
Quickly, keep quiet.

91
07:37.899 --> 07:40.600
- Egg head!
- Quiet!

92
07:40.600 --> 07:43.300
-Bullet head!
-Quiet!

93
07:44.600 --> 07:45.699
Keep quiet.

94
07:45.800 --> 07:48.000
-I didn't say anything!
-Quiet!

95
07:54.699 --> 08:00.699
I've called you out because Uncle Maxence
has just been wounded in a cowardly attack.

96
08:00.699 --> 08:04.399
According to our action-reactionprinciple,
the one responsible shall be severely punished.

97
08:05.100 --> 08:08.600
If the guilty one does not turn himself in
within 3 seconds,

98
08:08.899 --> 08:13.550
You will all take turns in jail, 6 hours each.

99
08:13.550 --> 08:18.199
Until he turns himself in or is denounced.

100
08:18.800 --> 08:22.500
One two three

101
08:23.500 --> 08:26.899
No one? Naturally.

102
08:26.901 --> 08:28.550
Come here.

103
08:28.550 --> 08:30.199
You, Mathieu

104
08:30.201 --> 08:30.999
Me?

105
08:31.000 --> 08:32.699
Come here.

106
08:32.700 --> 08:36.499
Mr. Chabert, give me the record book, thank you

107
08:36.500 --> 08:39.500
Mr. Mathieu, the new prefect,
is fortunate not to know you yet.

108
08:39.600 --> 08:41.100
Egg head!

109
08:41.100 --> 08:42.597
Be quiet.

110
08:42.600 --> 08:46.600
He will therefore decide impartially
who will be punished first.

111
08:49.600 --> 08:51.649
Be quiet!

112
08:51.651 --> 08:53.923
Pick a name.

113
08:53.924 --> 08:55.663
At random?

114
08:55.663 --> 08:57.399
If I may...

115
08:57.399 --> 08:59.798
Leave him. Go ahead

116
09:02.798 --> 09:04.700
Boniface

117
09:05.700 --> 09:09.399
Unlucky. Chabert, bring Boniface out.

118
09:09.399 --> 09:12.399
But, I didn't do anything!

119
09:12.399 --> 09:13.197
Shut up!

120
09:13.200 --> 09:16.000
It's unfair!
Shut your mouth! Let's go.

121
09:16.899 --> 09:18.298
I won't go!
I'll kick your ass if I have to!

122
09:18.301 --> 09:20.399
Quiet!

123
09:21.100 --> 09:24.899
In addition, as long as the criminal is at large,
recess is canceled,

124
09:25.100 --> 09:27.298
And visits are forbidden.

125
09:27.298 --> 09:29.798
I invite you to denounce him as fast as possible.

126
09:29.801 --> 09:32.499
This only encourages denouncing.

127
09:32.500 --> 09:36.750
Like all new-comers, you have generous illusions.
Let's talk again in a week.

128
09:36.750 --> 09:41.000
Until then have Mr Regent show you your quarters.
You're taking over from him.

129
09:44.899 --> 09:46.700
Clean sheets.

130
09:46.701 --> 09:48.200
Thanks.

131
09:50.399 --> 09:51.798
Why are you leaving?

132
09:53.500 --> 09:55.850
10 stitches

133
09:55.850 --> 09:58.197
Scissors.

134
09:58.200 --> 10:01.298
All this because I confiscated Mouton's cigarettes.

135
10:01.301 --> 10:02.197
Mouton?

136
10:02.200 --> 10:06.399
A kid. His name is Mouton.

137
10:06.399 --> 10:10.599
Is he still here, this Mouton?

138
10:10.600 --> 10:14.200
For your info, Le Querrec is the one who set the trap
on Maxence's door.

139
10:14.298 --> 10:16.298
I overheard him talking about it.

140
10:16.399 --> 10:17.500
Why did you keep silent?

141
10:17.600 --> 10:19.899
I don't want to miss the bus.

142
10:20.100 --> 10:22.600
Maxence punished him for breaking some window panes.

143
10:22.700 --> 10:26.100
It's a revenge. Just his style.

144
10:26.200 --> 10:30.700
Le Querrec, you have remember this name.

145
10:30.899 --> 10:33.798
And Morange, yes, Morange

146
10:33.899 --> 10:36.100
He speaks little, but you have to keep an eye on him.

147
10:36.200 --> 10:38.500
Angel face, but possessed by the devil.

148
10:38.600 --> 10:41.500
Action/reaction, that's all they understand.

149
10:46.000 --> 10:50.700
I'm leaving. Good luck!

150
10:50.701 --> 10:52.200
Thank you.

151
10:59.000 --> 11:00.798
Our benefactor.

152
11:00.899 --> 11:02.899
This is the class schedule.

153
11:03.000 --> 11:07.100
Classes were split between the headmaster,
doing history and French,

154
11:07.298 --> 11:10.899
while the rest was taught by a certain
Mr Langlois.

155
11:11.100 --> 11:13.500
Mr. Langlois, let me introduce our new prefect.

156
11:13.700 --> 11:14.798
My name is Clement Mathieu

157
11:15.000 --> 11:16.600
A prefect at your age?

158
11:16.700 --> 11:18.899
Yes, I was once a teacher.

159
11:19.100 --> 11:21.500
That is perfect.

160
11:24.700 --> 11:26.899
He's the funniest of the lot.

161
11:27.000 --> 11:29.100
Go to the study room now - You are late.

162
11:29.298 --> 11:31.298
No need to show you the way...

163
12:03.298 --> 12:04.899
Gentlemen.

164
12:09.899 --> 12:15.100
Smoking is forbidden in class, everyone, even you, sir.

165
12:21.200 --> 12:24.298
Give it back to me, quiet!

166
12:28.298 --> 12:31.100
Give it back to me.

167
12:33.100 --> 12:34.600
Good start!

168
12:34.700 --> 12:36.500
Congratulations. Mathieu

169
12:36.600 --> 12:38.200
Be seated.

170
12:40.200 --> 12:44.100
Naturally. You, always you.

171
12:45.200 --> 12:47.100
What did he do?

172
12:47.200 --> 12:49.700
Nothing. Headmaster

173
12:49.899 --> 12:51.700
What do you mean, nothing.

174
12:51.798 --> 12:53.298
Didn't you want to punish him just now?

175
12:53.399 --> 12:57.899
I was asking him to the blackboard,
and requesting silence when you came in.

176
12:58.100 --> 13:03.500
Indeed you needed silence.
Don't let me have to come back.

177
13:09.600 --> 13:11.899
Go to the corner.

178
13:13.298 --> 13:18.500
All right. Now that you know me better,
we need to set a few things straight.

179
13:20.500 --> 13:22.899
Right now, one of your fellow pupils is in jail.

180
13:23.000 --> 13:24.700
For nothing.

181
13:24.899 --> 13:28.500
I may not look smart,
but I was not born yesterday.

182
13:28.600 --> 13:30.500
I know who did it.

183
13:30.600 --> 13:33.700
I give him 15 seconds to confess.

184
13:36.700 --> 13:38.500
I am waiting.

185
13:40.700 --> 13:43.100
Too bad. Only 5 seconds left.

186
13:45.200 --> 13:46.899
Too late.

187
13:48.000 --> 13:51.600
Le Querrec, who is Le Querrec

188
13:52.600 --> 13:54.000
Me, sir

189
13:55.700 --> 13:57.798
What a coincidence.

190
13:58.000 --> 13:59.899
So, it is you who wounded Mr. Maxence.

191
14:00.000 --> 14:01.197
No. not me.

192
14:01.200 --> 14:03.100
I am not asking you. I am telling you.

193
14:03.100 --> 14:03.999
I did nothing.

194
14:04.000 --> 14:07.700
Who do you think the headmaster will believe,
you or me?

195
14:08.000 --> 14:12.100
While I am out, I would like someone serious
to watch over the class.

196
14:12.399 --> 14:16.000
If I believe my trusted intuition,

197
14:16.200 --> 14:17.600
this serious person is Mr Morange.

198
14:19.600 --> 14:22.500
Be quiet, who is Morange?

199
14:23.899 --> 14:25.798
Me, sir.

200
14:32.399 --> 14:34.798
So, you are the angel face

201
14:35.798 --> 14:38.700
Go to the blackboard.
You watch the class while I am out.

202
14:39.500 --> 14:40.798
Let's go!

203
14:41.798 --> 14:43.399
Nice attire.

204
14:43.399 --> 14:45.798
Pull your shirt out further,
it's more proper.

205
14:46.100 --> 14:49.700
Black sheep are said to have authority over their peers.
Prove it to me.

206
14:50.798 --> 14:53.298
Let's go. To the headmaster.

207
14:56.000 --> 14:57.399
Have mercy, sir.

208
14:57.399 --> 14:58.298
Mercy?

209
14:58.298 --> 15:00.200
Did you show mercy on the classmate
who is in jail instead of you?

210
15:00.298 --> 15:01.999
How about Uncle Maxence?

211
15:02.000 --> 15:04.298
I didn't want to harm him. It was just a joke.

212
15:04.301 --> 15:06.000
A joke?

213
15:08.000 --> 15:13.000
It's enough. Do you hear,
You'll get a good beating in my office.

214
15:17.500 --> 15:18.399
Who is that?

215
15:18.399 --> 15:21.500
It's Leclerc, he ran away for the third time.

216
15:22.500 --> 15:23.899
He will be sent to jail.

217
15:23.899 --> 15:25.798
This way you'll have a companion. Let's go.

218
15:25.899 --> 15:27.399
No.

219
15:29.399 --> 15:32.600
Listen. Maybe we can make a deal.

220
15:32.798 --> 15:35.100
You wounded uncle Maxence badly. Really bad.

221
15:35.298 --> 15:38.798
I will not bring you to the headmaster,
but I'll punish you.

222
15:39.298 --> 15:43.700
From now on, during recess,
you'll work in the infirmary.

223
15:43.899 --> 15:48.500
You will look after Uncle Maxence,
until he is recovered.

224
15:49.500 --> 15:50.899
Do you agree?

225
16:08.899 --> 16:11.100
Not bad, ah?

226
16:12.500 --> 16:15.600
I believe I can do better. Show me your profile.

227
16:16.298 --> 16:18.200
Profile.

228
16:31.100 --> 16:33.399
I give you a little smile for a change.

229
16:33.798 --> 16:36.000
There you go. Have a look.

230
16:36.200 --> 16:38.399
Ah, I forget.

231
16:38.500 --> 16:40.298
A little spot of colour.

232
16:43.298 --> 16:45.899
Does it look better? Go back to you seat.

233
16:47.500 --> 16:49.500
All right, in order to know you better,

234
16:49.700 --> 16:56.000
Please write down your name, age and what you want to do
when you grow up.

235
17:03.298 --> 17:05.099
To my surprise,

236
17:05.099 --> 17:07.099
all the pupils did as they were asked.

237
17:11.099 --> 17:13.000
Everybody, expect one.

238
17:17.400 --> 17:19.099
Aren't you writing?

239
17:21.599 --> 17:23.099
How long have you been here?

240
17:24.798 --> 17:26.900
A long time?

241
17:27.099 --> 17:28.798
I don't know.

242
17:30.798 --> 17:32.900
Come on, write, little boy.

243
17:48.298 --> 17:50.298
An exhausting first day.

244
17:50.400 --> 17:52.500
I don't know why I am here.

245
17:53.500 --> 17:55.798
Rachin scares me. This place scares me.

246
17:55.900 --> 17:58.200
Even the kids scare me.

247
17:58.298 --> 18:01.900
I feel they may run into my room at any time
and do me in.

248
18:01.901 --> 18:03.200
My blanket.

249
18:05.200 --> 18:09.098
Give me a puff.
Shut up. Go to sleep.

250
18:23.598 --> 18:26.098
I read what the pupils wrote.

251
18:26.700 --> 18:29.000
They were all dreaming of fabulous carreers.

252
18:29.200 --> 18:32.200
Two firemen, three cowboys, one tiger-tamer,
one fighter pilot

253
18:32.298 --> 18:34.900
two spies, a general under Napoleon.

254
18:35.000 --> 18:40.298
one hot air balloon pilot, three soldiers.
No prefect.

255
18:42.000 --> 18:44.700
It's very kind to volunteer to take care of me.

256
18:45.700 --> 18:49.798
See, doctor, the new prefect asked for a volunteer.

257
18:50.000 --> 18:53.298
And he responded. Spontaneously.

258
18:54.098 --> 18:56.200
This shows miracles do happen.

259
18:56.201 --> 18:58.798
Please come in.

260
18:58.798 --> 19:00.700
This is Mr. Mathieu, our new prefect.

261
19:01.299 --> 19:02.299
How are you
How are you

262
19:02.402 --> 19:03.201
How is he?

263
19:03.500 --> 19:09.598
It's quite a bad gash.
If now they come after you, hope is lost.

264
19:10.400 --> 19:12.798
You have such infinite patience towards them.

265
19:13.298 --> 19:14.499
I'm hard headed.

266
19:14.500 --> 19:18.098
The poor kids have it way worse than me here.

267
19:18.298 --> 19:20.000
One of them died here.

268
19:20.000 --> 19:21.199
One died?

269
19:21.200 --> 19:24.400
His name was Mouton.
Jumped from the rooftop.

270
19:24.500 --> 19:26.199
Fortunately, he was an orphan.

271
19:26.200 --> 19:29.400
Like him, everyone says nothing can be done.
But that's not true.

272
19:29.500 --> 19:32.700
He's a good boy.
You just need to know him.

273
19:32.900 --> 19:35.798
Uncle Maxence is kind, isn't he?

274
19:36.098 --> 19:38.298
Le Querrec, I am talking to you.

275
19:38.400 --> 19:40.798
Uncle Maxence is kind, isn't he?

276
19:43.098 --> 19:44.098
Yes.

277
19:44.200 --> 19:45.098
I can't hear you.

278
19:45.200 --> 19:48.798
Leave him alone. He is shy, just like me.

279
19:58.500 --> 19:59.499
Yes?

280
19:59.500 --> 20:00.598
I need to talk to you. Headmaster.

281
20:00.798 --> 20:04.200
You already want to leave?
No, I just want to do an experiment.

282
20:06.400 --> 20:08.900
About uncle Maxence's accident.

283
20:09.098 --> 20:10.400
That was no accident.

284
20:10.500 --> 20:13.298
Sure. I would like you to grant me three things.

285
20:13.400 --> 20:14.598
What?

286
20:14.700 --> 20:16.500
First, lift the collective punishment.

287
20:16.598 --> 20:18.900
Second, allow me to punish the guilty one.

288
20:19.000 --> 20:21.900
Third, please allow me to keep his name to myself.

289
20:22.400 --> 20:23.999
Provided you have the name.

290
20:24.000 --> 20:26.098
Of course, only provided I have it.

291
20:26.200 --> 20:27.999
You are arrogant, man.

292
20:28.000 --> 20:30.298
So, you believe you can find him just like that.

293
20:30.400 --> 20:33.598
Alright. If you succeed,
I'll lift the punishment.

294
20:33.700 --> 20:36.798
You'll never find the guilty party,
or I am the king of imbeciles.

295
20:38.598 --> 20:41.200
I know who did it, sir.

296
20:43.200 --> 20:47.000
Is that so. Who is it?

297
20:47.798 --> 20:50.000
You allowed me to keep his name a secret.

298
20:51.000 --> 20:53.900
Good, very good.

299
20:54.098 --> 20:55.500
But your methods irritate me.

300
20:55.798 --> 20:58.298
Don't let me find anything wrong with your class.

301
20:58.598 --> 21:00.598
I feel I already have them well under control.

302
21:00.700 --> 21:03.400
You speak too soon.

303
21:20.598 --> 21:22.597
These are not naughty pictures.

304
21:22.598 --> 21:24.400
I never said they were naughty pictures.

305
21:24.401 --> 21:26.298
What's written on yours?

306
