612
42:12.300 --> 42:14.500
She leaves you here to have peace.

613
42:14.800 --> 42:16.300
No, she has to work

614
42:16.400 --> 42:19.300
-Ah, so what the others say is true.
-What?

615
42:19.800 --> 42:21.800
She is a whore

616
42:26.800 --> 42:28.500
Get in!

617
42:30.500 --> 42:32.199
You're a dead man!

618
42:32.900 --> 42:34.699
Am I?

619
42:44.699 --> 42:47.300
That day, Morange was missing at the
3pm roll call.

620
43:25.300 --> 43:28.300
No one ever knew where he went,
but he came back.

621
43:29.300 --> 43:31.199
That's what mattered.

622
43:33.300 --> 43:34.900
Why are you here?

623
43:40.900 --> 43:42.599
I'm not allowed to go upstairs

624
43:43.599 --> 43:45.400
What do you mean?

625
43:46.800 --> 43:48.000
Why?

626
43:49.000 --> 43:50.199
Because I have no money

627
43:50.900 --> 43:53.699
You have no money, so you can't sleep?
What is this all about?

628
43:54.699 --> 43:59.300
It's Mondain.
If I don't give him money, he won't let me upstairs.

629
44:04.699 --> 44:05.800
We must be careful

630
44:10.000 --> 44:11.900
Where I was before I was
caught by the prefect.

631
44:12.300 --> 44:14.099
So I had to let him have it.

632
44:14.800 --> 44:16.199
How?

633
44:16.199 --> 44:19.300
Stabbed him with a bayonet. He bled well.

634
44:19.400 --> 44:21.800
-Did you kill him?
-You bet

635
44:21.900 --> 44:24.800
It's the same here.
Egg head better leave me alone.

636
44:25.099 --> 44:26.300
Mathieu is not the worst.

637
44:26.400 --> 44:28.800
Are you kidding?
Singing you a lullaby,

638
44:29.099 --> 44:33.000
Then when you sleep he will come and touch you.
This type must all be killed.

639
44:35.500 --> 44:37.500
Good evening, gentlemen

640
44:40.900 --> 44:43.000
-Have a good appetite!
-I swear I didn't do anything, sir!

641
44:43.699 --> 44:46.300
I see you have high-class friends, Corbin

642
44:48.300 --> 44:49.500
Get out!

643
44:57.199 --> 45:00.199
This feast I just witnessed will be our secret.

644
45:00.400 --> 45:01.599
Gift to you.

645
45:01.699 --> 45:03.099
But I warn you,

646
45:03.500 --> 45:07.300
Don't speak to Pepinot, don't approach him

647
45:07.699 --> 45:10.599
Don't even look at him, is that clear?

648
45:12.400 --> 45:17.099
A single look towards him and I'll turn
your life into a nightmare

649
45:52.900 --> 45:55.599
-What are you doing here, Morange?
-Nothing, sir

650
45:56.500 --> 46:00.199
I must have heard voices - I must be tired.

651
46:02.199 --> 46:06.599
Article 8 of school regulations:
students are not allowed into classrooms alone

652
46:07.000 --> 46:09.699
If it were Mr. Rachin, you would have to
write it a 100 times for tomorrow.

653
46:09.900 --> 46:11.699
Plus what he would tell your mother.

654
46:12.699 --> 46:14.500
I don't care about my mother

655
46:15.099 --> 46:17.000
-What did she do, tell me!
-I have nothing to tell you

656
46:17.199 --> 46:19.400
Wait! I'm not finished.
You won't get off that easily.

657
46:19.599 --> 46:22.400
Nothing is free here, ask Pepinot

658
46:23.800 --> 46:27.000
Your problem, Morange, is
that you do things that are unlike you.

659
46:27.099 --> 46:29.550
Run away, get into fights, play truant

660
46:29.550 --> 46:32.000
It may amuse the others, but not me.

661
46:32.500 --> 46:37.800
I won't play your little game.
From tomorrow, compulsory choir practice.

662
46:37.900 --> 46:40.000
And daily music class.

663
46:40.099 --> 46:41.699
Go, go to sleep

664
46:42.500 --> 46:43.599
Go

665
46:45.400 --> 46:46.699
March 3

666
46:46.800 --> 46:49.099
He cannot know, but I am sure of it.

667
46:49.300 --> 46:50.900
His voice is a miracle

668
46:51.099 --> 46:53.400
The rare promise of an exceptional musical gift.

669
46:53.599 --> 46:56.099
You can go now, keep quiet

670
46:58.099 --> 46:59.900
Keep quiet!

671
47:00.300 --> 47:02.800
Gradually, as my choir gets better

672
47:03.500 --> 47:05.300
I domesticate my new student.

673
48:26.099 --> 48:28.099
Ok, take your calculus notebooks

674
48:32.199 --> 48:35.400
You are the one who makes the children sing?

675
48:35.599 --> 48:38.000
Yes, isr
Are you complaining?

676
48:38.099 --> 48:41.000
Oh, no, on the contrary
I love music,

677
48:41.199 --> 48:44.199
-I sometimes myself croon
-Do you?

678
48:54.500 --> 48:55.998
Have a nice day!

679
48:56.000 --> 48:59.099
Same to you, my dear colleague

680
48:59.101 --> 49:01.900
Algebra book, page 27

681
49:34.900 --> 49:36.400
Hello, madam

682
49:37.900 --> 49:39.300
Pierre will come soon

683
49:39.400 --> 49:41.900
-What happened?
-Everything is fine

684
49:42.400 --> 49:44.000
How about his tooth?

685
49:44.199 --> 49:45.500
It got better

686
49:45.599 --> 49:48.099
Did you tell him I dropped by?

687
49:48.500 --> 49:51.300
-No
-Why?

688
49:51.500 --> 49:53.297
I preferred not to tell him.

689
49:53.300 --> 49:57.300
As you know, Pierre is a sensitive child,
and talented.

690
49:57.599 --> 49:59.599
a talent for mischief.

691
49:59.699 --> 50:01.599
Not only that,

692
50:01.800 --> 50:05.500
I must talk to you about it

693
50:05.800 --> 50:07.599
Singing? Nobody taught him?

694
50:07.800 --> 50:11.300
He has a gift. It's obvious.
Something must be done.

695
50:13.000 --> 50:14.500
Hello

696
50:15.500 --> 50:17.000
I'll leave the two of you.

697
50:17.599 --> 50:19.300
Don't hesitate to come and see me.

698
50:22.300 --> 50:26.900
I didn't tell your mother you were punished,
I told here you were at the dentist. No betrayal.

699
50:49.900 --> 50:52.300
-I'm told that you sing well?
-Yes

700
50:56.300 --> 51:00.500
The gentleman seems happy with you, is he kind to you?

701
51:01.500 --> 51:02.900
Not bad

702
51:06.099 --> 51:10.699
I brought you clean clothes,
and I made your favourite chocolate cake.

703
51:12.800 --> 51:14.099
Are you happy?

704
51:23.099 --> 51:26.199
April, the children inspire me.

705
51:26.400 --> 51:29.599
I knew the day would come when
my music would be played.

706
51:29.800 --> 51:35.400
I'm Clement Mathieu, musician,
every night, I compose for them.

707
53:19.099 --> 53:20.800
It was not good, sir?

708
53:20.900 --> 53:23.800
Yes, good, it was very good.

709
53:27.400 --> 53:29.599
You bastard! Go!

710
53:30.599 --> 53:32.000
What did he do?

711
53:32.099 --> 53:34.199
He stole my watch.
Caught him in my bedroom.

712
53:34.800 --> 53:37.000
Bringing him to see Rachin. Action-Reaction

713
53:37.500 --> 53:39.599
-Where are you taking him?
-Jail! 15 days!

714
53:40.599 --> 53:43.099
-Wait!
-Wait for what?

715
53:43.400 --> 53:45.500
He is my only barytone

716
53:49.500 --> 53:50.800
Mathieu!

717
53:51.000 --> 53:53.199
-What's the matter, sir?
-I found graffiti in the...

718
53:57.199 --> 54:00.000
Sorry, sir, just a loose shot

719
54:02.000 --> 54:03.400
Stand aside!

720
54:04.599 --> 54:06.300
Mathieu, Chabert,

721
54:09.300 --> 54:11.199
With me

722
54:13.199 --> 54:16.900
As the weeks pass, I score
new victories.

723
54:27.900 --> 54:29.800
Leclerc, we are still good friends, ain't we?

724
54:30.199 --> 54:31.699
Of course, why do you ask this?

725
54:31.900 --> 54:33.900
-5 plus 3?
-53

726
54:34.099 --> 54:35.800
-Are you sure?
-Of course

727
54:35.900 --> 54:36.699
Thanks!

728
54:56.699 --> 54:58.099
Maybe it's only an illusion, but

729
54:58.199 --> 55:01.599
It seems that even our headmaster is changing

730
55:47.900 --> 55:50.699
Look, Uncle Maxence

731
55:59.699 --> 56:02.699
Attention, don't move

732
56:02.900 --> 56:04.300
Smile

733
56:10.300 --> 56:13.500
Come on, come out, Mondain!

734
56:22.500 --> 56:25.099
It's finished, child

735
56:33.099 --> 56:35.199
Come on!

736
56:41.199 --> 56:43.300
Chabert, I just met Mr Rachin

737
56:43.400 --> 56:46.800
To tell him that Mathieu's choir is fantastic

738
56:47.300 --> 56:49.300
-I'm tired
-But you are alawys so tired, alright 29!

739
56:49.500 --> 56:50.900
And what was his answer?

740
56:51.099 --> 56:53.300
Get the hell out is what he told me.

741
56:54.099 --> 56:56.300
Where is Mondain?

742
56:58.300 --> 57:00.400
Didn't you notice he was missing before the run?

743
57:00.500 --> 57:02.199
He was at roll call this morning, Headmaster

744
57:02.300 --> 57:03.699
After that, he...

745
57:03.800 --> 57:06.000
Good, in this case, I forbid
all outside walks until the end of the year.

746
57:06.001 --> 57:08.800
-Did he take much money?
-All the money, around 200 thousands francs

747
57:08.900 --> 57:12.300
How do I pay suppliers now? How?

748
57:12.599 --> 57:14.099
I should never have accepted him in here.

749
57:14.199 --> 57:16.300
All this for a damn experiment!

750
57:16.500 --> 57:19.199
Just like you, with your music

751
57:22.199 --> 57:27.000
I needed coal delivered for hot water, it will be next week.
I call the police.

752
57:31.699 --> 57:32.800
What's the matter?

753
57:48.599 --> 57:50.300
I observe that singing makes them smarter, Mathieu

754
57:50.400 --> 57:52.000
They make great progress

755
57:52.099 --> 57:54.699
Headmaster, children have had
no warm water for three weeks

756
57:54.800 --> 57:57.400
Cold water is good for blood circulation.

757
57:59.800 --> 58:01.400
By the way, Mathieu

758
58:01.500 --> 58:03.300
No more choir.

759
58:04.699 --> 58:07.500
-But, Headmaster
-Thanks, Mr. Mathieu

760
58:08.000 --> 58:10.000
Police station, please

761
58:18.000 --> 58:19.699
I don't know yet about the choir

762
58:19.900 --> 58:22.099
But for the kids, we can use wood.

763
58:22.300 --> 58:24.300
We have no firewood at all!

764
58:29.500 --> 58:32.900
Headmaster's personal storage

765
58:34.400 --> 58:36.599
Chabert,Action-Reaction

766
58:36.800 --> 58:38.099
Chabert surprised me

767
58:38.199 --> 58:40.300
I thought he was Rachin's clone

768
58:40.400 --> 58:46.599
He actually is a nice man, who believes sports and music
are the cements of our society.

769
58:48.699 --> 58:51.800
With his help, I organize resistance

770
58:52.099 --> 58:54.199
Our choir becomes a clandestine affair.

771
59:16.900 --> 59:19.900
No, you always let up at the end of the sentence

772
59:20.900 --> 59:24.000
I'm asking one last time to detach
every note clearly.

773
59:24.500 --> 59:26.599
It's late, we'll work on this tomorrow

774
59:26.699 --> 59:28.500
We are not doing the second part, sir?

775
59:28.699 --> 59:30.099
I didn't teach you the solo part

776
59:30.300 --> 59:31.900
But I learnt it.

777
59:32.099 --> 59:34.199
You did?

778
59:35.201 --> 59:38.201
Ok, let's begin

779
01:00:19.400 --> 01:00:21.300
Come on, come out

780
01:00:22.300 --> 01:00:26.400
May 13th, 3pm, Mondain is back

781
01:00:39.800 --> 01:00:41.400
-Where is the money?
-I don't know

782
01:00:41.500 --> 01:00:44.199
-Who stole it?
-I don't know, not me

783
01:00:47.199 --> 01:00:48.800
What's happening?

784
01:00:49.199 --> 01:00:50.400
He is beating him?

785
01:00:50.500 --> 01:00:51.800
For half an hour

786
01:00:51.900 --> 01:00:53.199
Is he mad?

787
01:00:53.300 --> 01:00:55.300
He is wasting his time, the child
won't say anything at all

788
01:00:58.699 --> 01:01:02.400
Ok, let's start from the beginning

789
01:01:03.800 --> 01:01:05.800
Where is the money?

790
01:01:05.800 --> 01:01:07.500
Tell me!

791
01:01:09.500 --> 01:01:11.400
Where is the money?

792
01:01:14.199 --> 01:01:15.900
Let go!

793
01:01:16.599 --> 01:01:18.300
Let go!

794
01:01:21.300 --> 01:01:22.500
Calm down!

795
01:01:22.599 --> 01:01:24.400
Calm down!

796
01:01:25.400 --> 01:01:28.500
The child has just confessed,
I'll call back the police.

797
01:01:29.500 --> 01:01:34.400
You will get to know another residence, with
other wardens and bars.

798
01:01:53.500 --> 01:01:58.599
To avoid depressing the children,
we did not tell them about the Mondain affair.

799
01:02:00.500 --> 01:02:04.000
We told them he was sent back to his original school.
End of story.

800
01:02:05.000 --> 01:02:07.000
A hen

801
01:02:07.199 --> 01:02:10.099
Lays 84 eggs

802
01:02:11.099 --> 01:02:15.000
every year

803
01:02:17.000 --> 01:02:22.099
Well fed, with good housing,

804
01:02:22.500 --> 01:02:27.400
Ventilation and sanitation,

805
01:02:28.400 --> 01:02:32.400
It will lay 150 eggs

806
01:02:32.699 --> 01:02:38.500
How many more eggs can a farm girl obtain

807
01:02:39.099 --> 01:02:44.800
if she owns 9 hens?

808
01:02:59.199 --> 01:03:00.699
Nice day?

809
01:03:02.699 --> 01:03:04.900
It's good to have a bit of sun.

810
01:03:05.300 --> 01:03:07.300
Summer days are coming.

811
01:03:10.300 --> 01:03:12.400
You know, Pierre surprises me everyday a bit more

812
01:03:13.199 --> 01:03:14.400
Anyway, I..

813
01:03:14.500 --> 01:03:16.500
I wanted to thank you for what you do for him.

814
01:03:16.800 --> 01:03:19.199
I do it for you as well

815
01:03:19.400 --> 01:03:23.199
I mean, if Pierre is good,
so will you be...

816
01:03:26.599 --> 01:03:29.699
-Let me wipe it
-It's ok, it's ok

817
01:03:29.800 --> 01:03:34.599
-Just ink, nevermind
-You are too much! Idiot!

818
01:03:35.599 --> 01:03:38.500
What's the matter? Oh!

819
01:03:39.099 --> 01:03:41.199
Why do you beat him?

820
01:03:41.800 --> 01:03:43.599
Tell me, Bebert

821
01:03:43.900 --> 01:03:46.199
Because he threw ink at you

822
01:03:47.000 --> 01:03:49.000
Can't you shut up?

823
01:03:49.800 --> 01:03:52.400
Pierre, I'm ashamed of you.

824
01:03:54.699 --> 01:03:59.199
Wait! It's ok!

825
01:04:00.199 --> 01:04:02.599
You have to understand,
It's because he is proud of you and you are pretty

826
01:04:02.800 --> 01:04:04.000
Pretty?

827
01:04:04.099 --> 01:04:07.000
I mean, you are unusual comparing with
other children's mother

828
01:04:07.199 --> 01:04:09.000
Do you mean that I'm alone?

829
01:04:09.199 --> 01:04:10.900
Me too.

830
01:04:11.099 --> 01:04:13.199
-But you have no children
-No

831
01:04:13.300 --> 01:04:15.199
I have sixty

832
01:04:15.199 --> 01:04:18.400
But when they see you, they see the
lady of their dreams

833
01:04:18.500 --> 01:04:21.599
I mean, the mother they all dreamt about

834
01:04:21.800 --> 01:04:24.500
It's not a dream for Pierre, you are his mother

835
01:04:24.699 --> 01:04:27.199
Like all other children,
he doesn't want to share with others

836
01:04:27.400 --> 01:04:30.500
We must get him out of this boarding school where he's
wasting his time and send him to music school.

837
01:04:31.500 --> 01:04:33.599
I'd like him to have a real job.

838
01:04:33.699 --> 01:04:35.398
Music is a true career

839
01:04:35.400 --> 01:04:38.699
Provided one has solid grounding.
He could go to Lyons Institute of Music,

840
01:04:40.000 --> 01:04:41.900
I'd keep an eye on him so he does not stray.

841
01:04:42.099 --> 01:04:44.500
Even there, you can get a bad teacher

842
01:04:44.699 --> 01:04:49.800
-And then?
-Then, he will become whatever he must.

843
01:04:50.800 --> 01:04:52.099
Alone we can't do anything.

844
01:04:52.199 --> 01:04:55.000
Pierre is an exception. I will do everything in my power
so that his talent can bloom.

845
01:04:55.199 --> 01:04:59.699
- But it need your help, too
- I see, thanks

846
01:05:24.000 --> 01:05:27.900
No, no! What's the matter, today? Are you all sleepy?

847
01:05:28.199 --> 01:05:30.000
And you, Boniface, how do you stand?

848
01:05:30.099 --> 01:05:32.500
Do you think we can sing like this?
Stand straight!

849
01:05:33.300 --> 01:05:36.400
Ok, again, start from So gentle...

850
01:06:09.500 --> 01:06:11.699
Where is my solo?

851
01:06:11.900 --> 01:06:12.900
What solo?

852
01:06:13.000 --> 01:06:14.199
My solo!

853
01:06:14.400 --> 01:06:16.599
Ah, yes, your solo, no, no solo any more

854
01:06:16.800 --> 01:06:19.099
You have a decent voice,
but no one is indispensible.

855
01:06:19.300 --> 01:06:21.099
You sing or not. It does not matter to me.

856
01:06:21.199 --> 01:06:23.900
We can do without you. Listen.

857
01:06:24.300 --> 01:06:26.699
Listen, we start...

858
01:06:29.699 --> 01:06:31.500
We start from Oh, night

859
01:06:52.300 --> 01:06:53.599
Mathieu!

860
01:06:53.900 --> 01:06:57.099
-You're gonna get a scolding...
-I thought he had gone to town?

861
01:06:57.300 --> 01:06:59.800
Dismissed. Go play outside.

862
01:07:07.800 --> 01:07:10.199
You are a pain, do you know that?

863
01:07:10.400 --> 01:07:13.000
Headmaster, I promise you,
homework is finished

864
01:07:14.000 --> 01:07:16.500
Our charity committee heard of your choir

865
01:07:16.699 --> 01:07:18.297
The countess herself writes to me

866
01:07:18.300 --> 01:07:21.199
She and her friends are visiting next sunday
They want to listen

867
01:07:21.300 --> 01:07:22.599
It's great!

868
01:07:22.699 --> 01:07:24.099
I mean, it's good

869
01:07:24.199 --> 01:07:28.699
I already see the scene. Simpering,
music, why not petit fours since we're at it!

870
01:07:28.701 --> 01:07:31.900
You give me extra work with all these silly
things of yours!

871
01:07:33.500 --> 01:07:34.900
But, Headmaster, you will notice

872
01:07:35.000 --> 01:07:36.800
that Music has not relaxed discipline.

873
01:07:37.000 --> 01:07:38.500
We have had less problems for quite some time.

874
01:07:38.599 --> 01:07:39.498
Coincidence

875
01:07:39.500 --> 01:07:41.199
I don't believe in coincidences, Headmaster

876
01:07:41.300 --> 01:07:45.199
It looks that way. Who apart from you
would tell the foundation about the choir?

877
01:07:45.400 --> 01:07:46.500
It's me

878
01:07:49.300 --> 01:07:50.797
Do you know how to write?

879
01:07:50.800 --> 01:07:54.000
-Uncle Maxence probably thought he was doing a good thing.
-Spare me your explanations

880
01:07:54.199 --> 01:07:55.800
I don't like your ways, Mathieu

881
01:07:56.000 --> 01:07:58.000
I think you don't like much, Headmaster

882
01:07:58.199 --> 01:08:00.500
Mr. Rachin, someone for you
in the guest room!

883
01:08:02.900 --> 01:08:05.099
Let's talk about this later

884
01:08:07.699 --> 01:08:09.199
It's for you

885
01:08:10.199 --> 01:08:13.400
Sometimes I think we should have let
Mondain strangle him.

886
01:08:17.100 --> 01:08:19.898
Violette was thanking me for what I was doing for her son.

887
01:08:20.000 --> 01:08:21.600
She wanted to talk to me about it privately

888
01:08:21.699 --> 01:08:24.100
And tell me something important.

889
01:08:24.300 --> 01:08:28.000
Rendez-vous at Square Cafe, 20th, 4pm

890
01:08:29.000 --> 01:08:30.898
I wrote a letter to the Lyons Institute of Music

891
01:08:31.100 --> 01:08:32.500
I know the principal there

892
01:08:32.600 --> 01:08:34.199
He kindly answered

893
01:08:34.300 --> 01:08:37.800
he would be glad to audition your son,
and in case he is admitted,

894
01:08:38.100 --> 01:08:41.599
He would help him get a scolarship.

895
01:08:41.600 --> 01:08:45.800
-Things will be easier on that front from now on.
-Is that so?

896
01:08:46.800 --> 01:08:49.000
After I met you,

897
01:08:49.800 --> 01:08:53.300
My...my life...

898
01:08:54.300 --> 01:08:55.800
How to say?

899
01:08:56.800 --> 01:08:59.300
-Change totally?
-Exactly!

900
01:09:00.300 --> 01:09:02.100
It's all thanks to you

901
01:09:02.398 --> 01:09:03.699
I could not imagine...

902
01:09:03.800 --> 01:09:06.300
Same here. I had lost hope...

903
01:09:07.600 --> 01:09:10.800
I'm thinking, maybe I'm wrong to go too fast.

904
01:09:11.199 --> 01:09:13.398
Ah, no, trust me, no problem

905
01:09:14.398 --> 01:09:16.500
It's true that you brought me luck.

906
01:09:17.100 --> 01:09:18.398
Luck?

907
01:09:22.800 --> 01:09:24.398
I met someone,

908
01:09:26.100 --> 01:09:28.100
He is an eningeer from Lyons

909
01:09:29.100 --> 01:09:30.800
I met him at the cafe.

910
01:09:31.100 --> 01:09:33.500
He works around here on a bridge project.

911
01:09:40.000 --> 01:09:41.398
Are you ok?

912
01:09:42.398 --> 01:09:43.398
Fine

913
01:09:44.300 --> 01:09:47.600
It's a great opportunity, for you and Pierre.

914
01:09:49.500 --> 01:09:51.500
Don't get upset. I have to run.

915
01:09:51.800 --> 01:09:54.300
I'm love for the three of us to have
lunch together one of these days.

916
01:09:55.800 --> 01:09:58.398
You will tell him about Pierre? Please?

917
01:09:59.500 --> 01:10:01.100
Why not

918
01:10:03.100 --> 01:10:05.000
Ok, goodbye

919
01:10:05.699 --> 01:10:06.699
Goodbye

920
01:10:10.699 --> 01:10:12.898
Thanks for all you've done

921
01:10:15.100 --> 01:10:18.398
Oh, not a word to Pierre for the time being.

922
01:10:32.800 --> 01:10:34.800
Sorry, may I take the chair?

923
01:10:34.898 --> 01:10:37.699
-Of course
-Thanks

924
01:11:59.699 --> 01:12:02.199
Countess, I... glad... flowers.

925
01:12:02.500 --> 01:12:05.699
I did not catch everything,
but I get the intention.

926
01:12:06.000 --> 01:12:08.199
Thank you, my child

927
01:12:09.199 --> 01:12:11.500
Countess, please allow me to introduce you to Mr. Mathieu,

928
01:12:12.199 --> 01:12:14.699
Our prefect, who makes our dear children sing.

929
01:12:15.000 --> 01:12:16.398
Countess

930
01:12:16.800 --> 01:12:18.100
Please accept my compliments, sir,

931
01:12:18.199 --> 01:12:22.398
We follow with great interest the humane and sensitive
teaching methods of Mr Rachin.

932
01:12:22.500 --> 01:12:25.000
We thank you for your contribution
to these methods.

933
01:12:25.100 --> 01:12:28.300
By the way, who came up with the idea for the choir?...

934
01:12:28.600 --> 01:12:32.398
-Well...
-Mine, Countess, my idea

935
01:12:32.600 --> 01:12:37.000
It is a great pleasure, Countess, to help
such an understanding director.

936
01:12:37.699 --> 01:12:39.600
Alright. Make them sing.

937
01:12:42.199 --> 01:12:45.500
-Mr. Rachin is modest, he doesn't like praise
-That's right

938
01:12:46.300 --> 01:12:49.300
What will you sing, then?

939
01:12:49.500 --> 01:12:51.199
La Nuit, by Rameau, Countess

940
01:12:51.300 --> 01:12:53.600
That must be beautiful

941
01:12:56.800 --> 01:13:00.300
Excuse me, who is the boy standing aside?

942
01:13:00.600 --> 01:13:02.000
Is he being punished?

943
01:13:02.100 --> 01:13:06.100
That boy? He is an exception

944
01:13:06.500 --> 01:13:08.398
May I begin?

945
01:15:37.399 --> 01:15:40.399
And in the eyes of Morange,
who was following my rythm so well,

946
01:15:40.402 --> 01:15:45.601
I read many things. Pride,
happiness to be forgiven

947
01:15:45.603 --> 01:15:50.603
but also something new for him,
gratefulness.

948
01:15:52.199 --> 01:15:54.300
First day of summer

949
01:15:54.500 --> 01:15:56.300
Our choir welcomes a new member

950
01:16:01.300 --> 01:16:02.898
Sorry, I missed the link. My mistake.

951
01:16:03.000 --> 01:16:06.199
Go ahead.

952
01:16:58.800 --> 01:17:01.300
Come here, it's important

953
01:17:04.100 --> 01:17:05.800
I was scrubbing the toilet walls to
remove graffitis.

954
01:17:06.000 --> 01:17:09.699
I lifted a tile and found this

955
01:17:09.699 --> 01:17:11.898
-It's Corbin's harmonica
-And this

956
01:17:12.100 --> 01:17:14.398
At least 200 thousands francs inside

957
01:17:23.398 --> 01:17:25.500
No one knew where your cache was.

958
01:17:26.898 --> 01:17:29.398
Don't tell me you don't know how
the money got there.

959
01:17:30.398 --> 01:17:32.898
Do you know Mondain was expelled
because he was accused of the theft?

960
01:17:33.699 --> 01:17:35.699
I didn't know

961
01:17:36.000 --> 01:17:37.699
It's true - You did not know.

962
01:17:38.000 --> 01:17:39.600
Now I've told you

963
01:17:39.800 --> 01:17:42.898
What got into you?
What were you gonna do with the money?

964
01:17:43.898 --> 01:17:46.398
If I tell you, you won't repeat?

965
01:17:46.600 --> 01:17:48.199
No

966
01:17:48.398 --> 01:17:49.800
I swear

967
01:17:51.800 --> 01:17:54.000
I wanted to buy...

968
01:17:54.199 --> 01:17:56.199
Buy what?

969
01:17:56.398 --> 01:17:58.600
A hot air balloon

970
01:18:00.000 --> 01:18:02.500
We don't know who stole the money,
but it proves that Mondain is innocent

971
01:18:02.699 --> 01:18:04.898
He would never have left without the money.
That's obvious.

972
01:18:05.100 --> 01:18:06.898
We will look into it in 2 days time, after I come back.

973
01:18:06.899 --> 01:18:09.500
Mathieu, don't worry too much.

974
01:18:09.699 --> 01:18:11.699
If Mondain is not guilty this time, he would
have been another time anyway.

975
01:18:11.898 --> 01:18:13.800
Nothing can be done for such people, nothing.

976
01:18:14.000 --> 01:18:16.800
-How about justice?
-He's in the hands of justice now.

977
01:18:17.000 --> 01:18:18.500
Headmaster, wait for me!

978
01:18:18.699 --> 01:18:20.800
-Wait for me!
-Are you leaving too?

979
01:18:21.000 --> 01:18:23.398
I am catching a ride.
I am spending my vacation at my sister's.

980
01:18:23.699 --> 01:18:29.000
There is a piano there

981
01:18:38.000 --> 01:18:40.100
Do you know why Rachin goes to Lyons?

982
01:18:40.300 --> 01:18:43.300
I think he needs to discuss the budget with the committee.

983
01:18:44.600 --> 01:18:46.398
-Doesn't he?
-Yes

984
01:18:46.398 --> 01:18:50.300
But actually, his main purpose is to kiss ass
for promotion and a medal.

985
01:18:51.100 --> 01:18:52.898
Do you think he will succeed?

986
01:18:53.100 --> 01:18:57.300
Crafty as he is?
He will present an idyllic picture of the school,

987
01:18:57.500 --> 01:19:03.398
Hide the terrible things you know,
and take credit for the choir's success.

988
01:19:03.600 --> 01:19:07.600
-Success?
-I've heard it, it's very good.

989
01:19:08.000 --> 01:19:11.199
Sir, is it true Langlois and the principal
left together?

990
01:19:11.398 --> 01:19:15.199
Yes, Chabert and Carpentier took two weeks,
We are masters of the place.

991
01:19:15.398 --> 01:19:17.398
Then there is no course today?

992
01:19:18.398 --> 01:19:19.500
No

993
01:19:19.699 --> 01:19:22.500
-What shall we do?
-Take a nap

994
01:19:23.000 --> 01:19:26.000
No, I have a better idea

995
01:19:32.000 --> 01:19:33.500
Excuse me, you...

996
01:19:33.699 --> 01:19:36.898
-Your medal?
-Yes

997
01:19:37.898 --> 01:19:40.000
The bird is in the nest, Mr. Rachin

998
01:19:42.000 --> 01:19:44.100
I don't know how to thank you

999
01:19:46.100 --> 01:19:49.898
Headmaster, call for you...

1000
01:19:54.898 --> 01:19:56.600
Excuse me, I...

1001
01:20:18.398 --> 01:20:20.100
The fire started from the roof.

1002
01:20:20.300 --> 01:20:24.699
The blaze was eating up the sleeping quarters,
where the kids were last seen.

1003
01:20:24.898 --> 01:20:28.300
Sixty children killed, trapped like rats.

1004
01:20:28.500 --> 01:20:29.500
To Rachin

1005
01:20:29.600 --> 01:20:33.398
His promotion and medal are going up in flames
right in front of him.

1006
01:20:33.500 --> 01:20:35.398
But suddenly...

1007
01:21:23.398 --> 01:21:26.100
After lunch, we got out by the back door
near the vegetable garden.

1008
01:21:26.300 --> 01:21:29.000
So that Mary and the villagers would not see us, then

1009
01:21:29.500 --> 01:21:31.199
We went to the Lignon forest

1010
01:21:32.500 --> 01:21:34.199
Why did you go there?

1011
01:21:34.800 --> 01:21:36.898
We did an orientation game.
The kids loved it.

1012
01:21:40.699 --> 01:21:43.500
Suffice to say, uncle Maxence,
I'm extremely disappointed by your behaviour.

1013
01:21:44.500 --> 01:21:47.600
Headmaster, I assume the entire responsibility for this escapade.

1014
01:21:47.800 --> 01:21:50.398
Uncle Maxence never stopped trying to talk me out of it.

1015
01:21:51.000 --> 01:21:53.600
That's what I call a lack of conviction.

1016
01:21:53.800 --> 01:21:56.300
On the other hand, one could say we saved the children's lives.

1017
01:21:56.500 --> 01:21:59.699
Well, if you had not left the school unattended,
there would have been no fire!

1018
01:22:00.199 --> 01:22:03.398
I don't know why I'm still listening to you.

1019
01:22:03.600 --> 01:22:05.800
Ok, uncle Maxence, considering your seniority,

1020
01:22:06.000 --> 01:22:08.398
you will only suffer a suspension.

1021
01:22:08.699 --> 01:22:10.898
As for you, Mr. Mathieu, you are fired

1022
01:22:11.100 --> 01:22:12.898
for breaking the school rules.

1023
01:22:13.100 --> 01:22:15.300
If that's what you want, then fire me too!

1024
01:22:15.600 --> 01:22:17.100
It's not for you to decide.

1025
01:22:17.600 --> 01:22:20.898
Mr. Maxence, thanks for your kindness
But I believe children need you very much

1026
01:22:21.398 --> 01:22:25.600
Think about the children,
since this gentleman never does.

1027
01:22:27.600 --> 01:22:29.800
This is your due, here you are

1028
01:22:30.000 --> 01:22:32.500
You leave immediately by the 6pm bus.

1029
01:22:32.699 --> 01:22:36.500
-I forbid you to see a single one of you pupils.
-What do you mean?

1030
01:22:36.898 --> 01:22:39.898
Uncle Maxence, make sure of it.

1031
01:22:44.398 --> 01:22:49.600
Headmaster, before we part,
let me tell you what I think of you

1032
01:22:49.800 --> 01:22:51.100
I know, Mathieu

1033
01:22:51.300 --> 01:22:54.600
-You are incompetent, cruel.
-What about them

1034
01:22:54.800 --> 01:22:56.800
-They didn't choose to be here
-Neither did I

1035
01:22:57.000 --> 01:22:59.000
I never wanted to be an educator.

1036
01:22:59.199 --> 01:23:01.398
And don't tell me you were dreaming
of burying yourself in this god forsaken place.

1037
01:23:01.600 --> 01:23:02.898
You had other ambitions. Me too.

1038
01:23:03.100 --> 01:23:07.500
-You should not take out your failure on the children.
-You think I enjoy playing prison warden?

1039
01:23:07.699 --> 01:23:09.297
Someone must do it.

1040
01:23:09.300 --> 01:23:11.199
But go ahead, go to Paris

1041
01:23:11.398 --> 01:23:13.000
Go knock on the minister's door

1042
01:23:13.199 --> 01:23:16.300
Hello! I'm Mathieu, we must use true educators
not half wits.

1043
01:23:16.600 --> 01:23:21.000
Get in, fight, since you have faith!
Mathieu! Saint Mathieu!

1044
01:23:21.500 --> 01:23:24.300
You're a failed musician, a prefect

1045
01:23:24.800 --> 01:23:26.600
Just a small prefect,

1046
01:23:27.500 --> 01:23:30.600
What do you do in life, Mr Mathieu? I'm a prefect,
prefect, prefect, prefect, prefect!

1047
01:23:33.600 --> 01:23:35.100
You are a madman

1048
01:23:35.300 --> 01:23:38.398
I'm so tired, go to hell

1049
01:23:38.898 --> 01:23:41.398
On the contrary, I'm leaving it

1050
01:23:53.398 --> 01:23:58.100
I had hoped some children would brave the interdiction
and come say goodbye, but nothing.

1051
01:23:59.500 --> 01:24:03.199
These children's wisdom resembled indifference.

1052
01:24:04.000 --> 01:24:06.500
And Morange, anyway...

1053
01:24:38.398 --> 01:24:41.398
On the first piece of paper,
I see Boniface exquisite handwriting

1054
01:24:41.600 --> 01:24:44.699
And the one with wrong spelling, should be Pepinot's

1055
01:24:44.898 --> 01:24:48.699
And the one with music notes, that's Morange.

1056
01:24:49.100 --> 01:24:53.000
And this one, that one

1057
01:25:15.398 --> 01:25:17.600
Make them stop!

1058
01:25:17.800 --> 01:25:20.000
-They've locked the door

1059
01:25:23.398 --> 01:25:26.500
At that time, I felt a surge of happiness
and optimism.

1060
01:25:26.699 --> 01:25:29.199
I wanted to tell the whole world.

1061
01:25:29.398 --> 01:25:31.100
But who would have listened?

1062
01:25:31.300 --> 01:25:33.800
No one knows who I am

1063
01:25:34.800 --> 01:25:37.398
The great artist would soon crash back to earth.

1064
01:25:37.600 --> 01:25:43.100
I'm Clement Mathieu, a failed musician,
unemployed prefect

1065
01:25:43.300 --> 01:25:49.300
I'm Clement Mathieu, a failed musician,
unemployed prefect

1066
01:26:02.699 --> 01:26:04.300
After that?

1067
01:26:05.300 --> 01:26:07.500
He never got around to writing it.

1068
01:26:10.500 --> 01:26:13.100
But I, I can tell you

1069
01:26:15.100 --> 01:26:19.398
And Pepinot told me.
The next day, on my road back to school

1070
01:26:20.398 --> 01:26:23.000
My childhood memories came back to me.

1071
01:26:24.000 --> 01:26:26.600
After Mathieu was fired, my mother took me back.

1072
01:26:27.600 --> 01:26:30.898
We went to Lyons, where I was admitted to the Music School.

1073
01:26:31.898 --> 01:26:35.000
Engineer wanted me to be a boarder again,
My mother refused

1074
01:26:35.398 --> 01:26:37.199
And he left us

1075
01:26:38.199 --> 01:26:40.800
Chabert, Langlois and uncle Maxence united

1076
01:26:41.000 --> 01:26:43.300
And denounced Rachin's abusive methods towards the students

1077
01:26:43.898 --> 01:26:47.398
Children were questioned, Rachin fired.

1078
01:26:52.398 --> 01:26:55.898
Clement Mathieu continued to teach music
untill he passed away

1079
01:26:56.300 --> 01:26:58.500
He never tried to be famous

1080
01:26:58.699 --> 01:27:02.199
All he did, he kept to himself.

1081
01:27:02.699 --> 01:27:05.898
To him? No, not entirely

1082
01:27:09.600 --> 01:27:12.500
Mr. Mathieu!

1083
01:27:13.500 --> 01:27:16.000
Wait for me

1084
01:27:18.000 --> 01:27:20.500
Mr. Mathieu!

1085
01:27:25.500 --> 01:27:26.800
Why are you here?

1086
01:27:27.000 --> 01:27:28.600
Could you please take me with you?

1087
01:27:30.600 --> 01:27:32.000
Oh, I can't do that

1088
01:27:32.199 --> 01:27:34.500
You must go back to school,
otherwise you will be punished

1089
01:27:34.800 --> 01:27:36.398
-Please
-Shall we go?

1090
01:27:36.600 --> 01:27:38.100
Be right back

1091
01:27:38.300 --> 01:27:41.100
I cannot take you away

1092
01:27:41.300 --> 01:27:42.600
Go back

1093
01:27:42.800 --> 01:27:44.100
Go

1094
01:27:44.500 --> 01:27:46.100
Go

1095
01:28:10.199 --> 01:28:12.699
Pepinot was right to believe in it.

1096
01:28:12.800 --> 01:28:16.699
The day Mathieu was fired was a Saturday

1097
01:29:18.199 --> 01:29:21.199
To Violette

1098
01:29:22.199 --> 01:29:32.199


